      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The difference is often subtle, but if it feels like it might \"give out,\" that's a red flag for ligament damage that needs more than rest. For a typical sprain, a few days of consistent RICE and then gradual, careful movement is the cure. However, if you're waiting until next week, you risk chronic instability, so try a very gentle, non-weight-bearing range-of-motion exercise tomorrow to gauge the true extent of the injury.",
      "source": "target",
